{
  "_doc": "Per-locale ambient beds. Key = Background3D CAMERA_PRESETS preset_id (the locale's bg3d id). On locale enter, AudioMgr ducks the dominant Music Player track to AMBIENT_DUCK (14%) and crossfades this bed up on the Ambient bus; on exit it reverses. bed = un-prefixed res path; gain = ambient bus target as a fraction of Settings.bgm_vol. Omit a locale (or point at a missing file) to leave the Music Player untouched there — a silent no-op. Character-portrait presets (alberto/antonio/dante/elicia/frasier/john/nicola/sam) are NOT locales and are intentionally absent. Beds reuse the shipped drones + four bespoke room-tones (diner, cathedral, domestic, and the two vol5 drones); any locale can get a bespoke bed later without touching code.",
